## Documentation:
https://crazymax.dev/diun/

## Dockerfile with which the image running diun has been deployed:
Dockerfile

## To build the image from the Dockerfile:
docker build -t nombre_imagen:version . (path where the Dockerfile is located)
Docker, curl, and skopeo have been installed; if any more are needed, they can be added to the Dockerfile.

## Run the following script to deploy the diun docker container:
./01-Run-Diun-Email.sh
In our case, it has been deployed by passing the configuration through environment variables

## File provider where the images from the external repository that we want to observe are passed:
data/config.yml

## Script to execute each time we receive a notification for a new/update of an observed image:
data/diun.sh
